## Tech Stack

- **Backend:** FastAPI + SqlAlchemy + WebSocket (`app/`)
- **Frontend:** React 19 + TypeScript (`ui/src/`)
- **Tooling:** `uv`, `ruff`, `mypy --strict`, `pytest`, `coverage` â€” `make help` for all tasks

### Rules

- **Keep frontend and backend types in sync.**
- **Only use SQL when the task explicitly requires database queries.**
- **Do not run `cd /home/jeff/projects/multi-llm-chat && ` before every terminal command.** Your terminal defaults to the root of the project. This just causes confusion and constant confirm dialogs. *It also dangerously bypasses permissions*. Instead, run the command directly. For example, instead of `cd /home/jeff/projects/multi-llm-chat && make test`, just run `make test`.
- **Do not run `bash ` before commands in terminal.** The terminal is already bash. It causes the same issue as the rule above.
- **Use the built-in IDE tools before trying to use terminal for file commands.** Use `list_directory` instead of `ls`.
- **Use `edit_file` instead of rewriting files manually.**
- **Only use `write_file` for new files.** If a file created is too big for `write_file`, write a smaller file then use `edit_file` to add sections.
- **Never use terminal for creating or editing files.**
- **Do not wander the project needlessly.** Focus on your immediate task and avoid unnecessary context switching. You will forget your previous context if you switch too much.

